Peru:
Fujimori came for medical investigations once more to the hospital
Former president Alberto Fujimori was delivered on Tuesday to a public hospital to examine the muscle loss of his legs, informed his family doctor.
72 year-old Fujimori who sits out 25 years of custody because of offence against the human rights during his reign (in 1990-2000) has several illnesses, including tongue cancer who operates four spots and is under control.
Alejandro Aguinaga, Member of Congress and his personal doctor, said the television that Fujimori was examined during three days in the Peruvian hospital of Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas to ascertain the reason for his pains and the muscle loss in the lower body limbs.
Aguinaga commented that of his opinion could be pardoned after Fujimori for humanitarian reasons. Nevertheless, he did not wish this because he holds him for innocent.
He was operated four spots on tongue cancer and he has lost 18 kilos of weight. In addition other illnesses come like a heavy erosive gastritis, the doctor enumerated a cyst in the pancreas, kidney stones, high blood pressure and blood circulation problems in the legs.
Fujimori is since September, 2007 in the custody institution of Dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de la policía.
In April, 2009 he was condemned to 25 years of prison for the murder of 25 people by the Todesschwadron of the Peruvian army which acted during his reign secretly.
